content: Back in NYC! The energy here is electric. Still, the job hunt begins anew. Anyone know where the best coffee is around here?
Just turned 22. Reflecting on the year, I've learned that setbacks are just setups for comebacks. Now, back to coding my personal trading algo.
Spent the last few days diving into AI-driven code evolution. It's like tuning a piano—precision is everything.
Had a great chat with an old mentor over coffee. He gave some solid advice on how to approach quant firms. Now, to refine my pitch.
My trading algorithm now integrates blockchain for real-time insights. It’s rough around the edges, but it's a start.
My algo crashed during a simulated market test. Time to debug and find where the inefficiencies lie.
Joined a local tech meetup. Met some peers in the AI and trading space. Networking is key, even if it’s a bit awkward.
Submitted applications to several top-tier quant firms. Now, to wait and see. Fingers crossed.
Took a break from the grind to visit MoMA. Art has a way of reframing problems. I see my trading algo in a new light.
Progress! Managed to optimize my algorithm's performance by 15%. Small victories feel big when you're building from scratch.
Realized my risk management was lacking. Been reading up on advanced strategies to bolster my trading resilience.
Had an interview with a quant firm. It was intense, but I feel like I held my own. Now, to wait and see if they bite.
Just had coffee with a peer from the meetup. They shared insights on a new AI model that could revolutionize my trading algo.
Working on integrating that new AI model into my algo. It’s like adding a new instrument to the orchestra. Exciting times.
My algorithm’s performance tanked after the update. Back to the drawing board, but I’m not discouraged.
Finally, some good news: got a call back from the quant firm for a second interview. Looks like my pitch worked. Time to sharpen my skills.
Finally implemented the AI-driven error handling into my trading algo. It's a safety net now, but I'm hoping it catches more than just mistakes.
Had a breakthrough! My algorithm now learns from past trades to adjust risk parameters. It's like teaching a dog new tricks, but with code.
Just had another round of interviews with the quant firm. They're impressed with my progress on the AI integration. Fingers crossed for an offer soon.
Spent the last few days debugging my blockchain integration. It's now running smoothly, providing real-time market insights. Small steps, giant leaps.
Got an email from the quant firm. They want me for a third interview! Looks like my work on risk management paid off. Time to prep.
Met with my mentor again. He introduced me to someone working on a similar AI project. Collaboration could lead to some interesting developments.
Just received feedback from the trading sim. The AI-driven code evolution reduced my losses by 20%. It’s like watching my code grow up.
Had to pivot after a major market shift. My algo didn't adapt as quickly as I hoped. Time to refine the real-time analysis to be more dynamic.
Discovered a mentor program through the tech meetup. Applied to join. It could provide the support I need for my next phase of development.
The quant firm offered me the position! It's official—I'll be working on AI-driven market analysis. A dream come true, but the real work begins.
Just moved my trading algorithm to the cloud. The speed and scalability are mind-blowing. It's like my code just got a turbo boost.
Had a setback with the blockchain integration. It's causing latency issues. I need to find a balance between real-time insights and efficiency.
Joined the mentor program. First session was eye-opening. Got some invaluable feedback on my risk management strategy.
Refined my pitch to the quant firm based on mentor feedback. They're interested in my blockchain integration approach. Progress is real.
Just had my first day at the quant firm. It's exhilarating to see my work in a professional setting. The learning curve is steep but exciting.
